namedLocations.description: Arial, sometimes marketed as Arial MT, is a sans-serif typeface and computer font packaged with Microsoft Windows, other Microsoft software applications, Apple Mac OS X, and many PostScript computer printers. The typeface was designed in 1982 by Robin Nicholas and Patricia Saunders for Monotype Typography. Arial is also a typeface family comprising standard Arial (Arial Std) and variants, including Arial Black, Bold, Extra Bold, Condensed, Italic, Light, Medium, Monospaced, Narrow, and Rounded.

transcript.text: Start by selecting a text object on your page.
A toolbar will appear below the top panel, offering options to adjust styles, add effects, and modify positioning for text editing.
Double click on the text or click on the Edit button from the toolbar to edit it.
Type your message and use the toolbar to adjust size, alignment, or spacing.
Additionally, you can browse through a variety of fonts to find the perfect match.
To change colors, select an element and click the colored square above.
Use the Basic or Advanced color tools to choose a shade, or paste a hex, RGB, or CMYK code for precise color selection.
Use the Positioning tool to align and layer objects.
You can center a single object on the page or evenly space multiple elements for easy resizing and movement.
Just group the selected elements, then ungroup them when done.
To replace any image element in the design, just drag and drop a new image in place or use the replace button for seamless updates.
With the designer tool you have everything you need to customize and create effortlessly.
